<TEXT>
lawyers for a physician who contends she 
contracted aids from a contaminated needle said monday there would 
be no settlement with the city hospital agency and her negligence 
lawsuit would go to the jury 
we are committed to get this case through to a verdict as 
quickly as possible so that veronica prego can go on with whatever 
remains of her life one of pregos lawyers diane s wilner 
said outside the courtroom 
the end of the twomonthlong trial had appeared to be at hand 
on friday as testimony was interrupted for several hours while the 
opposing sides conferred in the chambers of justice aaron d 
bernstein of brooklyn state supreme court 
however the negotiations collapsed and pregos lawyers said the 
jury would decide the lawsuits outcome 
the trial was postponed monday because a juror became ill over 
the weekend testimony was scheduled to resume tuesday 
prego 32 contends she developed the fatal disease after she 
accidently pricked her finger on a needle that had been used to 
draw blood from an aids patient at kings county hospital on the 
night of jan 12 1983 
prego is suing the city health and hospitals corp and two 
physicians charging negligence 
