<TEXT>
the wonder years and steamy santa 
barbara are among the television shows headed for polish 
audiences under an agreement announced monday between polish tv 
officials and an american outlet 
the twoyear agreement between polish television channel 2 and 
annapolisbased conduit internationale films calls for provision of 
programming and selling of advertising for the station 
formerly one of polands two governmentoperated channels 
offering a slim variety of news current affairs and regional 
programs channel 2 has been converted into a commercial operation 
under polands new noncommunist government 
in a statement released with the announcement ci said it has 
reached an agreement with the new world international production 
company to provide the wonder years for channel 2 
other new world features heading for poland include the daytime 
soap opera santa barbara and the crimeadventure show wise 
guy 
poland has a population estimated at 38 million and about 10 
million households with televisions according to ci the only 
other eastern european country with a commercial station is 
hungary with a population of about 10 million 
conduit internationale is a subsidiary of nl technologies which 
has been involved over the past dozen years with several 
nonentertainment businesses in poland including clothing 
marketing and production and aircraft marketing 
