that opened the door to free elections he said 
whats the record there was no progress toward genuinely 
open free internationally supervised elections until the contra 
effort effectively was killed dukakis said what does that 
tell you 
acting the part of a reporter dukakis quoted bush as saying in 
the closeddoor luncheon with the governors that the defense budget 
may be cut further 
the governors were asking bush whom the country should fear as 
an enemy with the sudden turn of events in eastern europe 
he said the enemy is instability ok fine but then he 
said look weve already cut the defense budget substantially 
below projected levels and he said its probably going to be 
cut even further 
dukakis said he has been too busy digging massachusetts out of a 
fiscal hole lately to think about his postgubernatorial career he 
said he wants to remain involved in public affairs 
as for future runs for political office he said i dont 
think you ever say never to anything who knows 
