25 when the 60yearold publisher of the countrys only opposition 
newspaper is to be inaugurated for a sixyear term 
but he will become a member of the national assembly where 
sundays elections put the sandinistas in opposition 
for a year after the 1979 revolution that toppled the corrupt 
somoza regime ortega had shared podiums with mrs chamorro whose 
husbands assassination a year earlier helped ignite the sandinista 
revolution 
but she became disillusioned with the leftist sandinistas as 
they turned repressive and dogmatic and left the revolutionary 
leadership 
in 1981 with former president reagans blessing and support 
the contra rebel insurgency was launched us trade sanctions 
followed and before long the centrally planned poorly managed 
economy was in decline 
mrs chamorro then inherits a country wracked by inflation 
with a huge trade imbalance and will surely be seeking substantial 
us aid 
