history and perhaps the most closely monitored anywhere 
after overthrowing dictator anastasio somoza the sandinistas 
transformed the country into a revolutionary state redistributing 
wealth to poor peasants improving the literacy rate and 
nationalizing major industries 
the ortega government won strong support from the soviet union 
and cuba and was accused by the united states of trying to foment a 
communist revolution in neighboring el salvador 
but the embattled sandinistas recently abandoned strident 
socialism and with economic support from the soviet bloc 
decreasing sought closer ties with the united states 
their loss at the polls follows by just a few months the 
restoration of democracy in much of the east bloc and moves toward 
democratization in the soviet union itself 
