fewer than 2 percent of americans questioned 
in a new survey say they might try cocaine if it were legal but 
60 percent say they think someone else would 
threefifths of those questioned in the poll released today by 
the drug policy foundation said all drug use is immoral and should 
be illegal while 35 percent disagreed 
and 55 percent said they believe the bush administrations war 
on drugs is likely to reduce the drug problem while 36 percent 
favored legalization of less serious drugs along with an increase 
in drug treatment and education 
when given the choice between providing treatment and counseling 
for drug users or punishing drug users with fines andor 
