longez a type of homebuilt aircraft designed by burt rutan went 
down in heavy fog authorities said 
reids father made his film debut in 1910 quickly going on to 
become one of the silent movie eras biggest stars his career was 
cut short in 1919 when he was injured in a train crash and became 
addicted to the morphine doctors administered as a pain killer he 
died in 1923 at age 32 
the plane crashed shortly after takeoff from santa monica 
airport early monday and authorities said reid was flying solo 
the cause of the crash was under investigation by the federal 
aviation administration lifeguard capt don rohrer said visibility 
in the area was about threequarters of a mile 
the longez craft reid was flying is constructed mainly of 
styrofoam epoxy b1 fiberglass and plastics and is tailless and 
has a rearfacing engine owners and flight instructors have 
described it as fuelefficient and nearly stallproof 
rutan also designed the voyager plane that circumnavigated the 
earth in 1986 on a single tank of fuel and a new lowcost attack 
plane called the ares that he rolled out monday 
however rutan stopped selling longez kits in 1985 citing 
liability concerns planes have since been built from plans 
obtained from previous builders but authorities said it wasnt 
immediately known if reids plane was an original or a later copy 
