reliability despite thursdays failure 
the 44l rocket experienced a loss in power in a booster just 
after lifting off from the ariane launch pad in kourou french 
guiana technicians were unable to control the rocket and were 
eventually forced to abandon the mission 
the vehicle blew apart over the atlantic ocean 1 minute 41 
seconds into flight the first failure in an ariane flight since 
1986 and the fifth in 36 missions 
the two japanese satellites were valued by one of the companies 
the mitsubishi subsidiary space communications corp at more than 
600 million 
