management and personnel told the house armed services 
subcommittee on military personnel and compensation that failure of 
congress to agree to shift funds would be a disaster 
we get the hollowness and fall in readiness that the congress 
itself urged us very strongly to avoid jehn said 
this makes a pretty good case for the administration to work 
more closely with congress responded rep marilyn lloyd dtenn 
i suppose so jehn said 
rep arthur ravenel rsc suggested that perhaps the pentagon 
did not request the exemption back in august knowing that cuts in 
military personnel would be an emotional issue 
there is some validity in the premise that some people have 
that you all sidestepped the request for exemption at that time 
safe in knowledge youd be in pretty good shape politically this 
year with the reprogramming request ravenel said 
