<TEXT>
benjamin f schwartz a us navy attorney 
who helped prosecute a japanese general after world war ii for 
organizing the bataan death march has died he was 80 
schwartz died sunday of heart failure at his los angeles home 
said his widow lois 
schwartz was a navy prosecutor at the manila philippines trial 
of gen masaharu homma who was convicted of organizing the 1942 
death march on the philippines bataan peninsula homma was 
executed 
american and filipino soldiers defending bataan and corrgidor a 
rocky fortress in manila bay were defeated by japanese forces in 
april and may of 1942 under homma the japanese forced an 
estimated 60000 of the soldiers to march about 70 miles to prison 
camps about 10000 of the prisoners died of starvation and other 
mistreatment during the march 
schwartz joined the antitrust division of the justice department 
