manufacturer nearly 30 million 
attorneys for usx did not return telephone calls seeking comment 
on the friday ruling by the appeals court 
the supreme court last june ordered the appeals court circuit 
court to reexamine its ruling in light of the high courts june 5 
1989 decision in wards cove packing co vs atonio 
the wards cove decision said minorities could not rely solely on 
statistics to prove discrimination but must link the data to a 
specific corporate employment policy 
the decision also allowed companies to justify practices that 
appear to have statistically discriminatory by showing the policy 
was a reasonable employment policy 
in its recent ruling the appeals court determined that even 
under the new more restrictive guidelines the blacks in the 
classaction suit had proved discrimination in hiring practices 
the court found that because the positions at issue were for 
unskilled workers any ablebodied person should be competent to 
perform the job 
since the hiring process was subjective the interviews had a 
significantly disparate impact on blacks as the percentage of 
successful black interviewees was significantly less than the 
overall percentage of successful interviewees chief judge a 
