<TEXT>
pilots at trump shuttle the northeast airline 
service named after the billionaire developer who bought it last 
june have ratified a new contract agreement 
the fouryear contract was approved by the pilots over the 
weekend and announced by the airline monday it provides for wage 
increases averaging 10 percent this year and a total 15 percent 
over the next three years 
the contract also makes changes in work rules to allow greater 
scheduling flexibility and calls for the pilots to begin sharing 
increased costs of medical benefits in 1991 
nearly all the 227 pilots at trump shuttle which links new york 
with boston and washington formerly worked for eastern airlines 
real estate tycoon donald trump bought the shuttle service from 
miamibased eastern for 365 million 
ray grebey the shuttles chief labor negotiator said in a 
statement that the new agreement reflects the unique nature of 
hourly shuttle operations 
the wage hike for this year which depends on a pilots rank and 
averages 10 percent was effective feb 19 trump shuttle 
spokeswoman joan fudala said 
she said the changes in work rules will allow standby shuttle 
crews for example to be assigned to fly charter flights when 
passenger traffic doesnt require additional shuttle flights 
the new contract also replaces a twotiered wage structure for 
pilots with a single tier ms fudala said starting pay for all 
new pilots will be 26400 a year 
the contract calls for a retroactive 8 percent wage increase for 
july 18 1989 through jan 1 1990 for all pilots who formerly 
worked for eastern the wage hike reflects the result of 
arbitration between eastern management and the pilots 
trump shuttle pilots belong to the air line pilots association 
one of three unions that struck eastern last march pushing it into 
bankruptcy court reorganization eastern pilots and flight 
attendants halted their sympathy strikes last november but the 
machinists union is continuing its walkout 
contract negotiations covering the 280 flight attendants at 
trump shuttle are due to start around april 1 ms fudala said 
talks with machinists have been postponed pending a challenge from 
a rival group the aircraft mechanics fraternal association which 
is seeking to represent mechanics at trump shuttle 
