the stock markets increasingly bearish attitude 
toward securities brokers appears to have forced american express 
co to drop plans to reduce its stake in shearson lehman hutton 
inc the nations no 2 brokerage 
american express said monday it will inject 750 million into 
its shearson and increase its ownership of the troubled wall street 
house by purchasing new shearson stock 
the move would appear to be a significant setback for american 
express the financial services company had been trying for months 
to reduce its stake in shearson to below 50 percent so it could 
remove the troubled broker from its balance sheet and reduce its 
exposure to the sharp profits swings of wall street 
it sounds like american express is going to take over shearson 
lock stock and barrel said perrin long a brokerage industry 
analyst for lipper analytical securities corp 
the new plan will boost american express stake in shearson by 
an undetermined amount said american express spokesman matt stover 
it replaces a previous plan to shore up shearsons finances that 
would have reduced american express stake in the broker to about 
45 percent from 61 percent currently 
under the abandoned plan shearson would have sold 250 million 
worth of stock to its existing shareholders american express had 
planned to distribute its quota of shearson shares to american 
express shareholders 
the shearson share offering was dropped in light of unsettled 
conditions affecting the securities industry american express 
said in a statement 
in addition to the chapter 11 bankruptcy filing by the parent of 
drexel burnham lambert inc profits at many wall street firms have 
