while prices have plunged on the tokyo stock 
exchange in recent days traders and the government have been 
playing a waiting game on the key question of interest rates 
many analysts believe the government must raise rates to cool 
the inflationary fears that many believe are underlying the 
markets jitters but a rate increase could unsettle the market 
further because higher rates make stocks less attractive 
uncertainty hurts the market an interest rate increase will 
hurt the market the question is which will hurt more said 
robert alan feldman an economist for salomon brothers asian 
subsidiary 
the tokyo stock exchange suffered its secondworst daily drop 
ever on monday with the 225share nikkei stock average falling 45 
