reaching record highs at the end of 1989 
the index rallied 17 percent today after swinging sharply 
during the session 
many analysts and dealers are convinced that the bank of japans 
only option to help settle the market is to raise interest rates 
for weeks market speculation has been that japans central bank 
would raise its discount rate the interest it charges for loans to 
commercial banks 
analysts say such a move is needed to curb inflation which has 
been heralded by a rapidly increasing money supply and a severe 
labor shortage and to cool high stock and land prices that many 
see as signs of economic overheating 
expectations were that the move would follow the feb 18 
parliamentary elections it didnt and analysts attributed the 
major stock market slide that began the next day to uncertainties 
over interest rates 
in an interview monday bank of japan governor yasushi mieno 
reiterated the banks cautious stance on another increase in the 
discount rate which was raised three times last year 
now we have to see how these rising interest rates from last 
year will affect the economy we hope for a favorable result but 
if we find that the measures we have taken so far are not enough 
then we will have to move into the next step he said 
we are also listening to the views which we hear in the 
markets that if we raised the rate again at a time when stock 
prices are declining so sharply it would push the market further 
down he said 
