the japanese yen and will be a basis for calming down 
many analysts believe a vicious cycle of cheap yen cheap 
stocks and cheap bonds is behind the turmoil in the tokyo markets 
the decline of each one has accelerated the decline of the 
other two said johsen takahashi director of mitsubishi research 
institute inc 
if an interest rate increase strengthens the yen these analysts 
