<TEXT>
lotus development corp on tuesday unveiled a 
longpromised version of its popular 123 computer spreadsheet 
program for ibm mainframe computers 
the program 123m allows personal computer users to pull 
data from a mainframe computer file and transfer it directly into 
the 123 spreadsheet 
lotus and international business machines corp said the 
software could cut days off the the traditional procedure in which 
data from a mainframe often must be altered so that it may be 
entered into a 123 spreadsheet on a personal computer 
spreadsheet programs allow the display of rows and columns of 
figures or bar graphs to represent such things as a companys sales 
or profits they are among the most popular programs for personal 
computers and 123 is the leading personal computer spreadsheet 
the move into mainframes represents the second foray by the 
cambridge massbased company into software for other types of 
computers last month lotus introduced a spreadsheet program for 
workstations made by sun microsystems inc it also is believed to 
be developing a version of 123 for minicomputers made by digital 
equipment corp 
lotus and ibm signed an agreement in april 1987 to jointly 
develop a spreadsheet program for ibm mainframes the program 
originally was to be released in early 1988 other versions of 
123 also have suffered lengthy introduction delays due to 
programming bugs and other problems 
at a news conference lotus vice president frank moss said one 
possible use for 123m would be for a retailstore chain to 
transfer sales data from spreadsheets on personal computers in its 
stores to a mainframe computer at company headquarters 
ibm said sears roebuck and co is one of about two dozen 
companies that have been using a preliminary version of 123m 
since august 
users do not need to know the computer commands for the 
mainframe computer the lotus program automatically transfers data 
from personal computers to the mainframe and vice versa 
during the delay in introducing 123m a new type of computer 
setup may have reduced the need for the product some industry 
analysts say that setup involves a file server a highpowered 
desktop computer that acts as a central repository for a network of 
personal computers existing versions of 123 can run on file 
servers 
however rick sherlund an analyst at goldman sachs amp co said 
the new version of 123 should appeal to companies that have a 
mainframe computer in place and want to tie it to personal 
computers through the spreadsheet 
sherlund said 123m should account for less than 5 million of 
lotus estimated 1990 revenue of 750 million but he said its 
more significant from a strategic vantage point since it should 
allow lotus to maintain its foothold in major corporations 
their strategy i think is to basically cover all their bases 
and offer products that run across the broad spectrum of hardware 
installed in corporate america he said 
ibm will be the sole marketer of the program which is designed 
for use on ibms system370 computer line sherlund said he 
believes lotus will receive less than half the revenue 
the software which will be available next month ranges in 
price from about 15000 to 48000 depending on the size of the 
computer system in addition monthly licensing charges of 583 to 
1800 are assessed the companies said 
</TEXT>
