<TEXT>
benetton group spa announced tuesday that the 
federal trade commission has closed an investigation into the 
fairness of certain us business practices of the italian apparel 
maker and retailer 
the ftc informed benetton in a letter feb 5 that the matter had 
been closed and that it wouldnt initiate any proceedings against 
the company benetton said 
the investigation which began in late 1988 first came to light 
last june benetton disclosed in a prospectus for a sale of 
securities in the united states that the regulatory agency had 
undertaken a preliminary probe 
the government probe had been aimed at determining whether 
benetton should be considered a franchiser and therefore subject to 
federal franchise rules it focused on the companys relationships 
with owners of benetton boutiques in the united states 
benetton said in a news release it was gratified that the ftc 
has decided not to take action against the company benetton 
consistently maintained throughout the investigation that it wasnt 
a franchiser under the ftc definition and that it had not engaged 
in unfair or deceptive business practices 
a violation of franchise rules can result in civil penalties of 
up to 10000 a day the ftc also has the power to seek civil 
remedies in court on behalf of owners investors or others 
a number of us store owners previously alleged in bankruptcy 
court proceedings that benetton had acted unfairly and violated 
franchise rules and other statutes 
one store owner had threatened to file a class action lawsuit on 
behalf of all owners that have challenged the way benetton does 
business 
federal law requires franchisers to make detailed disclosures 
before selling a franchise franchisers must obey various federal 
laws intended to protect business owners from abusive practices 
some states also have statutes that apply specifically to 
franchisors 
benetton markets its colorful clothing for women men and 
children through independently owned benetton retail stores there 
are more than 700 benetton stores in the united states 
</TEXT>
