<TEXT>
b dalton bookseller on tuesday said it plans a 
chainwide launch of a discount program aimed at regular book buyers 
the announcement came a day after one of b daltons major 
competitors waldenbooks unveiled a new preferred reader 
program which rewards frequent buyers with discounts and extra 
services 
the b dalton booksavers club which begins march 5 is 
similar to the waldenbooks program the company said in a news 
release it had launched the booksavers club in dallas in 1988 and 
now would be offering it at all of its 800 stores around the 
country 
members in the b dalton club will be able to purchase 
membership cards for 10 entitling them to receive 10 percent 
discounts on all books bought for a year a special 5 introductory 
price will be available during march 
the booksavers club program will be supported by a mailing 
of specially produced custom catalogs to participating members 
said leonard riggio president and chief executive officer of the 
b dalton division of bdb inc 
riggio said in a news release the chain will be offering other 
instore programs in the spring 
waldenbooks owned by k mart corp said its program will start 
friday among other elements waldenbooks also will offer 10 
percent discounts to participants enrolling for 10 a year into the 
preferred reader program 
</TEXT>
