<TEXT>
the dollar rose against the japanese yen 
tuesday reaching an eightmonth high despite intervention by 
central banks while closing mixed against other currencies 
gold prices fell republic national bank of new york quoted a 
bid for gold at 40825 a troy ounce as of 4 pm est down 25 
cents from late monday 
thomas palladino a trader with amsterdam rotterdam bank in new 
york said the federal reserve sold dollars in new york an attempt 
to drive down the currencys value against the yen when the dollar 
reached the 14880 to 14885 yen level 
he said the intervention appeared to have little effect 
earlier the bank of japan tried to stem the dollars rise 
against the yen in the tokyo market on monday both central banks 
likewise sold dollars but the currency reached an eightmonth high 
against the yen despite the intervention 
the dollar rose tuesday to 14873 yen in late trading in new 
york the dollar has not closed that high against the yen since 
june 15 when it reached 15130 yen 
traders said us currency softened a bit in the morning after 
the commerce department reported that orders to us factories for 
durable goods plunged 105 percent in january the biggest decline 
since orders first were tracked 32 years ago 
but the dollar soon regained its strength palladino said 
it really was a nothing trading day said bob morrissey a 
trader for bank of boston 
in tokyo the dollar rose to a closing 14903 yen from 14865 
yen at mondays close later in london it slipped to 14857 yen 
the dollar was mixed against the british pound in london the 
pound traded at 16915 late tuesday cheaper than 16927 late 
monday in new york the pound cost 16908 more than the 16903 
of late monday 
other late dollar rates in new york compared with late rates 
monday included 16880 west german marks down marginally from 
16882 14840 swiss francs down from 14860 57150 french 
francs up from 57140 124875 italian lire up from 124850 
and 11938 canadian dollars down from 119405 
late rates in europe compared with late mondays prices 
included 14857 swiss francs down from 14865 57010 french 
francs down from 57205 18985 dutch guilders down from 19023 
124525 italian lire down from 125025 and 11908 canadian 
dollars down from 11975 
on new yorks commodity exchange gold for curent delivery 
dropped 70 cents an ounce to 408 
earlier gold traded in london at a late bid price of 40725 a 
troy ounce down from 41175 bid late monday in zurich the bid 
price was 41125 unchanged from late monday in hong kong gold 
fell 430 to close at a bid 40785 
silver bullion closed in london at a bid price of 511 a troy 
ounce down from mondays 523 in new york silver for current 
delivery fell to 5075 an ounce from 5147 monday on the 
commodity exchange 
