<TEXT>
the price of mcclatchy newspapers incs 
publiclytraded common stock jumped sharply tuesday in heavier than 
normal activity 
mcclatchy class a common stock surged 3 to 2450 a share on 
the new york stock exchange on volume of 46900 shares compared 
with average daily volume of about 12600 shares 
asked if there was any explanation for the activity elaine 
lintecum corporate financial analyst for mcclatchy said it was 
the companys policy not to comment on trading activity in its 
shares 
on feb 20 the company made a similar statement in response to 
an inquiry from the nyse about that days trading activity on that 
day the class a stock rose 225 to 2162 a share on volume of 
62800 shares 
mcclatchy which is based in sacramento calif has two classes 
of stock 
its class a shares each carry onetenth of a vote and elect as a 
group 25 percent of the mcclatchy board as of dec 31 there were 
43 million class a shares outstanding 
the company also has 25 million shares of class b stock which 
are not publicly traded and are controlled or held for the benefit 
of the mcclatchy family each class b share has a single vote and 
the class b shares as a group elect 75 percent of the board 
the company owns 11 daily and eight nondaily newspapers 
including the sacramento bee the fresno bee and the anchorage 
daily news 
in 1989 the company earned 339 million or 119 a share on 
revenue of 3808 million up from a profit of 288 million or 
102 a share on revenue of 3558 million in 1988 
