three disciplinary actions linked to alleged 
trading violations were announced by the chicago board of trade and 
its affiliate the midamerica commodity exchange 
matthew daen a principal of am investors was suspended from 
membership priviledges for 10 days and fined 15000 he was 
accused of conduct inconsistent with just and equitable 
principles and trade and with other violations 
am investors was fined 10000 based on the incidents involving 
daen 
lawrence pfeifer a former floor clerk for am investors was 
denied floor access privileges for 10 days and fined 5000 he was 
accused of dishonest conduct and other alleged violations 
pfeifer declined to comment when reached at his home calls late 
tuesday to am investors went unanswered and no telephone listing 
was available for daen 
