after the indictment was announced the governor was much gentler 
with the justice department 
i want to make it clear that i never thought the justice 
department was proceeding in bad faith i dont think that they 
meant to harm us in any way cowper said 
in fairness to justice they were in a box here they were not 
able to give us the full story because the law prohibits them from 
disclosing whats going on in a criminal action before an 
indictment 
though thornburgh was upset with the states public criticism 
cowper said we felt we had to defend our position 
cowper said he would withhold comment on the indictment until he 
could read it 
